summary: Comprehensive testing of Kamch Aam Parikshan Ayurvedic health assessment application completed successfully. All core features are working correctly including assessment form, score calculation, result display, admin panel, and data export functionality.

design_issues.issue: Console warnings about controlled/uncontrolled state switching
design_issues.impact: No user impact, React development warning only

passed_tests: Landing page loads with proper styling and navigation
Assessment form - user info collection (name, age, gender, date, mobile)
Assessment form - all 14 questions with 5 options each
Assessment form - score calculation and result determination (14-28, 29-42, 43-70 ranges)
Result page - displays score, result interpretation, and personalized Ayurvedic advice
Contact/callback request form submission via API
Admin dashboard - view all assessments with stats cards
Admin dashboard - search functionality by name and mobile
Admin dashboard - filter functionality by result type
Backend API - all 15 endpoints tested with 100% success rate
Frontend-Backend integration - assessment submission and result display
Error handling - validation for missing fields
Navigation - between questions, back to home, new assessment
